<br>
I still think a better solution (to part of the problem that removing flags is supposed to address) is an extension of the system that lets 15% of a raid be unflagged.<br>
<br>
For tier 2-3 zones, let unflagged people hunt there if X people in the group are flagged.  Then you won't have as many trains and such (as dropping the flags entirely), yet people will still be able to hunt with their friends.  Gaining access to tier 2-3 zones will still be an accomplishment but missing a flagging event or not having the time to complete quests will not separate friends so much.<br>
<br>
Backflagging is an entirely separate issue which people have been addressing here already. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=senchy>Senchy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/14/03 9:38 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Acceptable Compromises to Flag Removal</span><hr size=1> There might be a much easier solution to address the concerns, both giving the casual/small guild folks more options to grind and second helping the mid/high end guild with a reward for going through the flagging and avoiding blown trigger mobs.<br>
<br>
Run two copies of the problematic zones. E.g. Two zones which are both Tactics, two zones of HoH. One of these zones is accessable by everyone, the other still requires the correct flagging or 85%. Add additional stones to pick which version of HoH/Tactics you want.<br>
<br>
With this, the casual players/small guild can have access to more grind zones, small/mid guild can still try bosses out of order.<br>
<br>
The mid-high end guild can have protected flag spawns by going into the zone version that requires the correct flags with spawn that cannot be blown by a casual grind group, e.g. HoH trials. Additional as a reward for the full flagging the flagged people have a less crowded version of tactics/hoh available to them.<br>
<br>
I have not though it through fully which zones would be need to be run as doubles.<br>
<br>
 <p>Senchy Solariatus <br>
65 Crusader of Rodcet Nife<br>
65 Chanter of Rodcet Nife (Tymbor)<br>
Dol Amroth<br>
<br>
