<br>
For a mid-level guild the current progression is a problem.<br>
<br>
We've done the work to get flagged for HoH, BoT, Torment, PoNb, CoD and everything below them via the key quests<br>
<br>
(And until you've done a few of the key quests please don't go thinking that being raidbot #59 on some massive raid makes you an uber player of some sort.  Go kill the medallion droppers in PoS with two groups, it's a very different style of play!) &lt;/rant off&gt;<br>
<br>
We could probably get some more flags by joining multi-guild Zerg events, but our guild only fields about 3 groups of 65 as a maximum and we like to play as a group.<br>
<br>
For us EQ is getting boring.  <br>
<br>
We can handily kill everything in the game, except for the zone bosses that take huge numbers...  We don't like playing in huge numbers... there's ZERO chance we can kill the Zek's (say) with 18 people... and there's lots of content we would love to chew on that's on the other side of some of those bosses.<br>
<br>
A key quest that let us work our way into some of that content without having to change our style of play would be a great improvement for us.<br>
